# Build context ignore rules for docker/Dockerfile.local ONLY.
#
# BuildKit automatically uses this file instead of the repo-root .dockerignore
# when the build targets this Dockerfile (`-f docker/Dockerfile.local`).
# It does NOT merge with the root .dockerignore — it fully replaces it, so this
# file must list every pattern the local build needs.
#
# Unlike the root .dockerignore, the local image builds from source with
# `npm run build` and never reads git, so we CAN drop `.git` and `chip` here.
# Do not remove `.git` from the root .dockerignore: Dockerfile.dev stamps the
# dev image version from git (scripts/version.mjs git) and needs it in context.

# Not needed by the local build (saves ~150 MB of context)
.agents
.claude
.devcontainer
.env
.git
.github
chip
docker
!docker/Dockerfile.local
!docker/Dockerfile.local.dockerignore
!docker/entrypoint.local.sh
docs
reflector
screenshots
scripts
systemd
**/vitest
*.md

# Dependencies
**/node_modules/

# Test output
**/coverage/

# Build output (rebuilt inside the image)
**/dist/
**/build/
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Tooling caches
**/.cache/

# VS Code settings
**/.vscode/

# Logs
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/pnpm-debug.log*

# Other assets not needed for builds
docker-downloads-history.json
tmp
temp
jest
**/tmp/
**/temp/
**/jest/
**/*.tgz
